Henry Earl DUNLAP, Petitioner, v. The WARDEN, United States Penitentiary, McNeil Island, Washington, Respondent. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 12, 1940.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and MATLIEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the petition for leave to file an appeal in forma pauperis in the above-entitled cause, it is ordered that said petition be, and hereby is, denied, as the appeal is without merit. 28 U.S.C. A. § 832.
